dct_description_sm: Map of the English coast from Dover to Epple Bay. Relief shown by hachures; depths shown by soundings and isolines. At head of title: England, S.E. coast. "1828." Historic Maps copy has labels on verso: "East Coast of England. Downs, with South and Queens Channels, with Views" and "No. 1828."
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : Published according to Act of Parliament at the Hydrographic Office of the Admiralty ; sold by R.B. Bate, agent for the Admiralty Charts, 21 Poultry and Royal Exchange, July 16th.1847.
